synopsis: Kusuo Saiki was born with supernatural powers. Thanks to his laid-back parents, he lived a fairly normal life. However, it turns out that having supernatural powers isn't really all it's cracked up to be.
Although Kusuo's parents are currently fighting each other, he tries to stay out of it since he thinks that it is a problem that they need to work out for themselves.
Kusuo's telepathic abilities allow him to read the thoughts of everyone around him. Everyone, that is, except for one particular individual...

title.jp: Shikkoku no Tsubasa Koto Kaidou Shun

synopsis: Shun Kaidou is another one of Kusuo's classmates at PK Academy. He claims to have special powers and believes that there are dark forces at work that have evil plans for humanity.

Kokomi Teruhashi is the quintessential pretty girl, leaving all the guys awestruck by her beauty and her sweet-as-honey personality. However, her attempt to bless Kusuo with her presence leads to some unexpected results.
It's dodgeball time in Saiki's PE class. As usual, Saiki tries to conceal his abilities, but his attempts to keep a low profile lead to unexpected difficulties.

Now that Hairo is out of the game, Saiki is the Paper Team’s last hope to win. However, Saiki is more concerned with figuring out how to keep his likability neutral so that he does not attract attention.
Chiyo Yumehara, one of Saiki’s classmates, has a crush on him. In order to get to know him better, she comes up with some plans to get closer to him.
Now that Saiki’s parents have reconciled, they want to sleep in the same bedroom. In order to do so, they need to move some furniture around and want Kusuo’s help.
Have you ever wondered why none of the other students have called attention to Saiki’s unique looks? It all has to do with a little bit of mind control...
Saiki comes across a self-proclaimed magician named Uryoku Chouno.
When Chouno appears on TV to do a death-defying stunt, Saiki rushes in to save him only to wind up in the middle of the stunt himself.
Saiki observes someone taking advantage of Kaidou's delusions to take advantage of him.
Saiki ends up going to the beach with his classmates.
Saiki starts to notice Nendou acting strangely, worried that he is up to something illegal.
Saiki is approached by another genuine psychic, Reita Toritsuka, who has the ability to see ghosts.
Reita's ability to see ghosts catches the attention of his fellow students.

title.jp: Hairo Kineshi no Mokusai o Motomete

synopsis: Kineshi drags Saiki into helping to finish a gate for an upcoming school festival.
While watching over the house, Saiki comes up against his one weakness; a cockroach.
With Chiyo in a rut with her new boyfriend, Saiki attempts to keep them together so she won't turn her attentions back to him.

title.jp: Muteki no Meisaifuku de Dasshutsu seyo!

synopsis: Saiki attempts to use invisibility to sneak past his classmates and get home in time for his favorite TV show.

title.jp: Moeta! PK Gakuen Taiikusai (Zenpen) (燃えろ！PK学園体育Ψ

synopsis: The students of PK Academy participate in a sports day event.

title.jp: Moeta! PK Gakuen Taiikusai (Chuuhen) (燃えろ！PK学園体育Ψ

synopsis: Saiki's powers nearly go out of control when Nendou accidentally removes one of his suppressing hair ornaments.

title.jp: Moeta! PK Gakuen Taiikusai (Kouhen) (燃えた！PK学園体育Ψ

synopsis: Saiki is forced to try and get his class to win to avoid getting a buzzcut.
The school ends deal with a fire drill with unconventional means.
Saiki ends up buying an expensive coffee jello.

title.jp: Saiyaku ni Awanai Tame ni wa...

synopsis: Saiki observes Kaidō getting conned by a fortune teller.
Kokomi accompanies Saiki, Nendou, and Kaido to a suspicious looking ramen restaurant.
Reita uses his links with spirits to search for a girl's missing gym clothes.
After having a foreboding dream, Saiki takes action to prevent a chain of events that will cause an explosion.
Saiki comes across a cat stuck between some walls, refusing to help him until he properly asks for it.
Hearing about how Nendou's never been visited by Santa, Kuniharu decides to dress up as him.
Saiki's parents become excited when they come across Kaidou and Harai during a New Year's shrine visit.
As everyone is invited over to the Saiki household, Kurumi accidentally blurts out that Saiki is a psychic.
Saiki is forced to rewrite his classmates' memories of the previous day, which comes with its own downsides.
Saiki stumbles upon some students planning to trick the strict PE teacher, Matsuzaki.
Saiki observes the boys' various reactions surrounding Valentine's Day chocolate.
Saiki is bothered by the ghost of Nendou's late father.
Saiki is forced to try and help Kurumi, whose trusting nature leads her to be constantly deceived by scammers.
Saiki comes across a ring that blocks his telepathy, which he hopes to use to watch a movie without any spoilers.
Kokomi's superstar brother Makoto shows up at Saiki's house to warn him to stay away from her sister, revealing that he has a disturbing sister complex.

title.jp: Sai o Fure! Haran no Kimatsu Tesuto

synopsis: While Saiki uses his telepathy to cheat during exams, Nendou gets help from his father.
Saiki reluctantly becomes Chouno's assistant in his magic show.
Chouno's show takes a turn for the worst when Nendou offers to be his assistant in a body-cutting routine.
Saiki helps out his poor classmate, Chisato Mera, who is secretly working various part-time jobs.
As the students take part in a physical fitness test, Hairo keeps getting outperformed by Nendou.
Realising that the cat from before, Anp, is likely in heat, Saiki transforms into a cat to try and help him confess to a female cat.
Since most mainstream video games are spoiled for him, Saiki ends up playing a shoddily made RPG, becoming frustrated by all the hallmarks of a crappy game.
Kaidou fears the worse when his mother invites Saiki and Nendou into their home.

title.jp: Kokuhaku no Saiteki!? Kuchiyose no Jutsu

synopsis: Reita tries to confess to a girl he likes by having other spirits possess his body.
A young boy named Yuuta Iridatsu believes Saiki to be a superhero named Ciderman No. 2 after witnessing his abilities.

title.jp: Saioote Ichiryuu Kigyou!? Chichi no Oshigoto

synopsis: Kuniharu shows Saiki around his job at a manga editorial office.
Yuuta, who is now Saiki's neighbor, comes over to watch an episode of Ciderman No. 2.
Saiki becomes livid when a pickpocket steals his wallet at a summer festival.
Kokomi and Chiyo meet up with each other, with both girls starting to suspect that the other likes Saiki.

title.jp: Katsu no wa Dotchi!? Unmei no Hankime

synopsis: As the class prepare for a school trip to Okinawa, Kokomi and Chiyo try to join Saiki's group.
After Saiki manages to prevent Makoto from going on the school trip with him, a typhoon puts the entire trip in danger.
Saiki deals with all kinds of troubles during his class' flight to Okinawa.
Upon arriving in Okinawa, Kaidou is eager to show off his knowledge of the Kansai dialect.
While Saiki takes a nap after keeping the boys from peeking into the women's bath, Kokomi removes one of his hair ornaments, leading him to do something to the hotel in his sleep.
After returning the hotel for normal, Saiki has to search for Kokomi, who had taken his ornament.

title.jp: Saiaku na Aru Yoru no Dekigoto in Okinawa

synopsis: Saiki ends up stuck with Kokomi, who believes she is in a dream.
As the class visits the beach, Chiyo gets annoyed when she gets no reaction to her swimsuit.
Chiyo comes to admire Kaidou after he protects her from some beach delinquents.
Saiki attempts to get a limited Coffee Red Bean Anmitsu before his school trip ends.
A transfer student named Aren Kuboyasu struggles to hide his past as a former delinquent.
Kuboyasu attempts to make friends with his classmates.
Saiki reluctantly helps Nendou's father profess his love to his wife.
The café Chisato works at tries to find ways to renovate to avoid going out of business.
Influenced by a detective drama, Kaidou looks into an alleged theft case at school.
Saiki's class tries to decide what to do for the school festival.
Reita ropes Saiki into helping out his band, whose members can't play any instruments.

title.jp: Sawage! PK Gakuen Bunkasai (Zenpen) (さわげ！PK学園文化Ψ

synopsis: As the school festival gets underway, Saiki loses his glasses blocking one of his powers and turns Nendou into stone.
Saiki has to try and keep the petrified Nendou from being discovered or broken.
Saiki, Kaidou, and Nendou get lost on their way to a wrap-up party.

title.jp: Saikyou Bishoujo vs Zettai ni Ochinai Otoko (Zenpen) (Ψ強美少女VS絶対に落ちない男

synopsis: In order to avoid Makoto's drama shoot, Saiki ends up going on a date with Kokomi in the neighboring town.

title.jp: Saikyou Bishoujo vs Zettai ni Ochinai Otoko (Kouhen) (強美少女VS絶対に落ちない男

synopsis: Saiki tries to avoid running into Makoto, leading to his date with Kokomi getting unwillingly extended.
Saiki gets roped into acting as Santa Claus and delivering presents around the neighborhood.

title.jp: Saishin Kaden o Kai ni Ikou!

synopsis: Saiki goes to buy a new television but gets pestered by the sales clerk.
Saiki deals with all the pains that come following the New Year.
Kaidou starts to suspect Kuboyasu of being a delinquent.
Kuboyasu saves Kaidou from delinquents.
Nendou and Kaidou challenge each other to a game of air hockey.
Nendou gets a part-time job to buy a present for his mother.
A 10 kilometer marathon takes place at PK Academy.
Teruhashi visits the Saiki residence under the alibi of receiving cooking lessons from Saiki's mother and spends time with Yuuta as well.

title.jp: Ocha no Ko Saisai! Warashibe Chouja

synopsis: Saiki does not have the funds to pay off a meal, so he uses a technique called Straw Millionaire, which involves apporting items with others of a similar value. This leads to disastrous effects with other characters.
Anp chokes on a piece from a model robot and Saiki becomes small in order to save him. Saiki can not change back to normal size until an hour's time is up.
Kongou is a delinquent Year 3 student at PK Academy. He has been held back and he changes his ways, with the help of Saiki's telepathy, so as not to be held back again.
The class goes for karaoke at a restaurant and Saiki orders a chocolate parfait to complete before it is his turn to sing.
Saiki goes to his grandparents house while on vacation with his family, and has to deal with his grandfather who has trouble showing his true emotions.
Saiki's grandfather is still happy about his daughter and grandson coming over to visit.
Saiki and his family go to a run down Amusement park that is falling apart.
Saiki's vacation at his grandparents house comes to an end, but Saiki's grandfather try's to do whatever he can to get Saiki and his family to stay.

title.jp: Shuku Gameka! Saitou Kunio no X Dan

synopsis: Saiki plays Kunio Saito's Horror Stories (a parody of the Saiki game which had recently been released).
Toritsuka becomes popular with the girls by letting ghosts possess him.
Toritsuka tries to create his own club in order to attract girls.
During Saiki's Home Economics class he teams up with Kaidou and Hairo to try making crepes.
Saiki is abducted by members of Teruhashi's fan club.
While walking with Kaidou and Nendou, Saiki notices that everyone seems to be talking about things that are connected to the number 100, but he can’t quite figure out why.
The control device for Saiki's powers gets broken.
The Saiki Family goes to London to get the control device fixed by Saiki's older brother, but get side tracked by Kusuo's parents sightseeing.
Kuusuke (Kusuo's brother) a genius who's never beaten his little brother at anything comes up with a plan to try to beat him.
Saiki, Nendo, and Kaido play a game of tag in London against Kuusuke.

title.jp: Bijutsukan de wa Saiteigen Oshizuka ni

synopsis: Saiki, Nendo, and Kaido go to an Art Museum in London.

title.jp: Natsuyasumi Mae no Sainan: Natsuyasumi Massaichuu! Occult Bu Gasshuku Hen

synopsis: With Summer Break just about to start Saiki will try to avoid having any plans during the break.

title.jp: Natsuyasumi Massaichuu! Tennis Bu Gasshuku Hen

synopsis: The Occult Club holds a test of courage in a forest. After that, Saiki's off to the Tennis Club's training camp.
Nendo teams up with Saiki in a tennis match against Hairo, then Saiki and Nendo join Mera in a clinical testing job.
After finishing the clinical testing job, Saiki goes to the motorcycle license training camp with Kaido and Kuboyasu.
On the last day of summer break, Saiki has a date to the amusement park with Teruhashi. However, Saiki brings Yuta along.
A new school term has started and Saiki's class has a new rich transferred student who intends to get Teruhashi to date him.
When Teruhashi turns down Saiko's love confession, he starts making life difficult for the people around her.
Saiki's grandparents come and visit Saiki's family. When they all go out, Saiki's grandfather's mean behavior towards his father leads him to be left alone in a strange place.
Kaido invites his friends to a Halloween party at his place.
In order to have his new classmates under his thumb, Saiko first tries to buy out Nendou by taking him out for a nice restaurant and offering him money.
Saiki learns that the magician Chouno has become a popular magician/comedian.
Yumehara gains a lot of weight and tries to lose it with the help of Saiki's Hypnosis.
Everyone is ignoring Saiki, and he discovers that it's because they are planning a surprise birthday party for him.
Saiki's "friends" plan him a surprise birthday party for him, however it is actually Saiki's father's birthday.
Saiki's father pretends to be Kusuo so that his "friends" don't feel bad about planning a birthday party on the wrong birthday.
